    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-05-19T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-05-19T08:00:00-05:00" n="553"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d553">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">751G.00/5–1954: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">United States Delegation</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret<lb/>priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-05-19T14:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 19, 1954—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Dulte1">Dulte</gloss> 86. Repeated information Paris 295. Eyes
                    only Ambassador Paris. <persName corresp="#p_CJ1">Chauvel</persName> states
                    privately <persName corresp="#p_BG1">Bidault</persName> somewhat concerned by
                    fact he cannot be in on impending French–US talks in Paris and thinking of
                    suggesting they be held here between him and me. Reminded <persName
                        corresp="#p_CJ1">Chauvel</persName> that military aspect of talks and other
                    reasons made it desirable to have them in Paris and will talk with <persName
                        corresp="#p_BG1">Bidault</persName> at early <pb facs="0880" n="854"
                        xml:id="pg_854"/> opportunity to see how seriously he takes this. <persName
                        corresp="#p_EPG1">Ely</persName>—<persName corresp="#p_TTJH1"
                        >Trapnell</persName> talks<note n="1" xml:id="d553fn1">For documentation on
                        the talks held between Generals <persName corresp="#p_EPG1">Ely</persName>
                        and <persName corresp="#p_TTJH1">Trapnell</persName>, see <ref
                            target="frus1952-54v13p1">volume <hi rend="smallcaps">xiii</hi>
                        </ref>.</note> should not take place here. My own feeling is that talks
                    should be held in Paris, with <persName corresp="#p_BG1">Bidault</persName> kept
                    fully and currently informed through me, allowing him time to express his views
                    before decisions are reached.<note n="2" xml:id="d553fn2">The Department of
                        State in telegram <gloss target="#t_Tedul1">Tedul</gloss> 97, May 20,
                        replied as follows: “Concur your views <gloss target="#t_Dulte1"
                            >Dulte</gloss> 86 re location talks and your informing <persName
                            corresp="#p_BG1">Bidault</persName>.” (Conference files, lot 60 D 627,
                            <gloss target="#t_CF1">CF</gloss> 242)</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SWB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
